---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { CRISIS_TEXT_EN, MEDICAL_DISCLAIMER_EN } from '../../lib/site';

const jsonLd = [
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'WebPage',
    name: 'An Nhịp privacy policy',
    inLanguage: 'en',
    lastReviewed: '2026-07-21',
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  lang="en"
  altPath="/quyen-rieng-tu/"
  title="Privacy policy | An Nhịp"
  description="An Nhịp keeps all your data locally on your device: no server, no account, no tracking. Details on what is stored, how it is protected, and how to delete it."
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
      <p class="muted">
        Applies to the An Nhịp app (m-Mental-Health) on Android. Last updated:
        21 July 2026. This content faithfully reflects the "Your privacy"
        section shown inside the app.
      </p>

      <h2>Summary</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Your data stays on your device.</strong> Data is stored
          locally (local-first). The app does not send data anywhere on its own;
          a research file leaves your device only when you choose to export it.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>No sign-in needed.</strong> The app does not collect your name,
          email, phone number or identity.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>You are in control of your data.</strong> Nothing is saved by
          default. You can delete the data the app manages at any time.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What data is stored on your device</h2>
      <p>
        The app saves an exercise session only when you complete that session
        and actively tap Save. A session you abandon, or choose not to save, is
        never recorded. A saved session may include:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>The exercise type (breathing, grounding, thought record) and when you did it (date only, no time of day).</li>
        <li>Your anxiety level before and after the exercise, if you choose to enter it. This field can always be left blank.</li>
        <li>Your heart rate, if you choose to enter it manually. This field can always be left blank.</li>
        <li>The thought record text you write, if you choose to save that session.</li>
        <li>The emotion you pick in the daily mood check-in.</li>
        <li>App settings (for example the app lock and your consent choices).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What data is not collected</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>No name, email, phone number, contacts or any identifying information.</li>
        <li>No location, camera, microphone.</li>
        <li>No server: the app has no backend, no cloud sync, no account.</li>
        <li>No analytics SDK, no ads SDK, no behavioral tracking.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Extra layers of protection</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Sensitive data is excluded from your device's cloud backups.
        </li>
        <li>
          To protect sensitive content, the app blocks screenshots and hides
          content in the recent-apps list.
        </li>
        <li>
          Every sensitive action (saving a session, entering heart rate,
          exporting a research file) goes through its own consent step. No path
          skips this step.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Research data export</h2>
      <p>
        If you take part in the thesis research, you can export a summary CSV
        file to send to the research team yourself. The export only happens when
        you consent and tap export yourself. The exported file uses a random
        participant code, never linked to your real identity, and
        <strong>never contains thought record text</strong>. The app's data
        structure is designed so the export query physically cannot reach the
        raw text you wrote.
      </p>

      <h2>Deleting data</h2>
      <p>
        In the app's Settings, you can delete all data the app manages at any
        time. Note: files you have exported or shared outside the app are not
        deleted along with it. Uninstalling the app also deletes all local data.
      </p>

      <h2>Medical note and emergency support</h2>
      <p>
        The app is developed for academic purposes within the scope of a thesis.
        {MEDICAL_DISCLAIMER_EN}
      </p>
      <p class="note note--crisis">{CRISIS_TEXT_EN}</p>

      <h2>Policy changes and contact</h2>
      <p>
        When the policy changes (for example when the app is released on Google
        Play), this page will be updated with the new effective date. For any
        privacy question, you can reach us through the project's source page on
        <a href="https://github.com/tranhoavn-max/an-nhip-web" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
